\title{Gf3 Pr Verify}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Verify GF(3) skill conservation on pull requests. Ensures every contribution}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) PR Verification}
\p{Enforces skill coloring requirements on all contributions. PRs without valid GF(3) manifests will be rejected.}

\subtree{
\title{Why GF(3) Conservation?}
\p{Every contribution uses skills. Recording which skills were used:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Provenance}: Track how code was created}
\li{\strong{Balance}: Ensure generator/validator equilibrium}
\li{\strong{Reproducibility}: Others can use same skill triads}
\li{\strong{Attribution}: Credit skill authors}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Required PR Format}
\p{Every PR body or comment MUST include:}

\pre{\startverb
## GF(3) Skill Coloring

| Skill | Trit | Color | Role |
|-------|------|-------|------|
| skill-name-1 | ⊕ (+1) | #RRGGBB | Generator |
| skill-name-2 | ○ (0) | #RRGGBB | Coordinator |
| skill-name-3 | ⊖ (-1) | #RRGGBB | Validator |

**Conservation**: Σ = (+1) + (0) + (-1) = 0 ✓

Thread: ⟨xxxx⟩
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Trit Definitions}
\pre{\startverb
| Trit | Symbol | Value | Role | Hue Range | Examples |
|------|--------|-------|------|-----------|----------|
| PLUS | ⊕ | +1 | Generator/Executor | 0-60°, 300-360° (warm) | gay-mcp, gaymove, depth-search |
| ERGODIC | ○ | 0 | Coordinator/Synthesizer | 60-180° (neutral) | acsets, aptos-agent, ducklake-walk |
| MINUS | ⊖ | -1 | Validator/Constrainer | 180-300° (cold) | code-review, narya-proofs, three-match |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Conservation Rules}
\subtree{
\title{Rule 1: Single PR Conservation}
\pre{\startverb
Σ trits ≡ 0 (mod 3)
\stopverb}

\p{Valid combinations:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb ⊕ ⊗ ○ ⊗ ⊖\stopverb} → 1 + 0 + (-1) = 0 ✓}
\li{\code{\startverb ⊕ ⊗ ⊕ ⊗ ⊖ ⊗ ⊖\stopverb} → 1 + 1 + (-1) + (-1) = 0 ✓}
\li{\code{\startverb ○ ⊗ ○ ⊗ ○\stopverb} → 0 + 0 + 0 = 0 ✓}
}

\p{Invalid:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb ⊕ ⊗ ○\stopverb} → 1 + 0 = 1 ≠ 0 (mod 3) ✗}
\li{\code{\startverb ⊕ ⊗ ⊕\stopverb} → 1 + 1 = 2 ≠ 0 (mod 3) ✗}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rule 2: Cross-PR Triads}
\p{PRs can form balanced triads across the repository:}

\pre{\startverb
PR#23○ ⊗ PR#24⊕ ⊗ PR#25⊖ ⊢ Σ = 0 ✓
\stopverb}

\p{Document cross-PR links:}

\pre{\startverb
### Cross-PR Triad
This PR (⊕) balances with:
- PR#XX (○) - coordinator
- PR#YY (⊖) - validator
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Rule 3: Thread Linkage}
\p{Include thread ID for provenance:}

\pre{\startverb
Thread: ⟨6d21⟩
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Verification Commands}
\subtree{
\title{Check PR Body}
\pre{\startverb
# Extract and verify GF(3) from PR
gh pr view $PR --json body | jq -r '.body' | \
  grep -oE '[⊕○⊖]' | \
  awk 'BEGIN{s=0} {if($0=="⊕")s+=1; if($0=="⊖")s-=1}
       END{m=(s%3+3)%3; print "Σ="s" mod3="m; exit(m!=0)}'
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Check All Open PRs}
\pre{\startverb
# Verify all open PRs have GF(3) manifests
for pr in $(gh pr list --json number -q '.[].number'); do
  echo -n "PR#$pr: "
  gh pr view $pr --json body | jq -r '.body' | \
    grep -q 'GF(3)' && echo "✓" || echo "✗ MISSING"
done
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Generate Skill Manifest}
\pre{\startverb
# List skills used in this session
cat << 'EOF'
## GF(3) Skill Coloring

| Skill | Trit | Color | Role |
|-------|------|-------|------|
| gf3-pr-verify | ⊖ (-1) | #3541C7 | Validator |
| code-review | ⊖ (-1) | #3541C7 | Validator |
| gay-mcp | ⊕ (+1) | #FFD700 | Generator |

**Conservation**: Σ = (-1) + (-1) + (+1) = -1 ≡ 2 (mod 3) ⚠️
Need 1 more ⊕ or 2 more ⊖ to balance
EOF
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{CI/CD Integration}
\p{Add to \code{\startverb .github/workflows/validate.yml\stopverb}:}

\pre{\startverb
- name: Verify PR GF(3) Conservation
  if: github.event_name == 'pull_request'
  run: |
    PR_BODY=$(gh pr view ${{ github.event.pull_request.number }} --json body -q '.body')

    # Check for GF(3) section
    if ! echo "$PR_BODY" | grep -q 'GF(3)'; then
      echo "::error::PR missing GF(3) Skill Coloring section"
      exit 1
    fi

    # Verify conservation
    SUM=$(echo "$PR_BODY" | grep -oE '[⊕○⊖]' | \
      awk 'BEGIN{s=0} {if($0=="⊕")s+=1; if($0=="⊖")s-=1} END{print s}')
    MOD=$((($SUM % 3 + 3) % 3))

    if [ "$MOD" -ne 0 ]; then
      echo "::error::GF(3) not conserved: Σ=$SUM (mod 3)=$MOD"
      exit 1
    fi

    echo "✓ GF(3) conserved: Σ=$SUM (mod 3)=0"
\stopverb}
}

